@node intro "Introduction"

 What is it for?

	Fast and small filelister for Dialog. Mainly for make AGuide lists.
	ATTENTION! You need KickStart 2.04 or higher.

@endnode

@node using "Using"
	
	DiaGFlist [-a] [-l] [-n] name

	-a = Build AmigaGuide List.
	-l = Description length (default 40).
	-n = List n old files.

	Examples: DiaGList -a -l50 -n3 Ram:NewFilesA.Txt
		  DiaGList -n3 Ram:NewFiles.Txt
		  DiagList Ram:AllFiles.Txt
	
@endnode

